      "solution": "let n = int_of_string (input_line stdin) in\n\nlet mult = ref 1.0\nand exp = ref 0 in\n\nfor i = 1 to n do\n  mult := !mult *. float_of_int i;\n  while !mult >= 10.0 do\n    exp := !exp +1;\n    mult := !mult  /. 10.\n  done\ndone;\n\nPrintf.printf \"%.2f\" !mult;\nprint_string \"*10^\";\nprint_int !exp;\nprint_endline \"\";",
      "statement": "Given an integer n, compute the factorial of n, or the product of all integers from 1 to n :\nn! = 1 x 2 x 3 x ... x (n-1) x n\n\noutput format : [[float]]{{*10^}}[[exponent]], where :\n    - [[float]] is a floating point number between 1 (inclusive) and 10 (exclusive)\n    - [[exponent]] is a positive integer\n[[float]] should be rounded to and shown with 2 decimal places.\n\nFor example :\n> 6 should be printed as 6.00*10^0 (= 6 * 1)\n> 240 should be printed as 2.40*10^2 (= 2.4 * 100)\n> 12345 should be printed as 1.23*10^4 (number gets rounded to 12300)\n> 1000000 should be printed as 1.00*10^6",
